caption.text:
Brand masterclass from McDonald’s.

I actually hate unhinged marketing. So many brands are doing it that it’s just become boring and feels more and more ‘fake’. How can every brand have the same exact strategy and tone of voice on social. But nonetheless there are lessons to be learned here. 

 #instagramgrowth #socialmediamarketing #branding #marketing

caption.text:
Should creators be paid for making content? 

I actually don’t have much skin in the game as I make my revenue from my products and services, and I don’t think any of the platforms are perfect. But I do think YouTube treats it’s creators best and I believe there is value you in this. In the same way that when music distributors like Spotify fail to pay artists for their work, we all lose out. It costs money to be an artist. It’s why most actors come from wealthy backgrounds (because so few others can afford to pursue it full time). By paying creators, it’s the creators that come form underprivileged backgrounds that stand to benefit the most. It might just give them the time and space to make the content they want to make without having to worry about where their next meal will come from.

I might just be a hippy, but I do wish IG had a more win-win approach and philosophy to rev share. Right now they’re the worst in class. Below YouTube, TikTok, and even X in many instances. 

#instagram #instagramupdate #contentcreators
